verses.text: These \add be\add* the words which Moses spake unto all Israel on this side Jordan in the wilderness , in the plain over against the Red \add sea\add*, between Paran , and Tophel , and Laban , and Hazeroth , and Dizahab.\f + \fr 1.1 \ft the Red…: or, Zuph\f*
(\add There are\add* eleven days’ \add journey\add* from Horeb by the way of mount Seir unto Kadesh-barnea.)

And it came to pass in the fortieth year , in the eleventh month , on the first \add day\add* of the month , \add that\add* Moses spake unto the children of Israel , according unto all that the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* had given him in commandment unto them;
After he had slain Sihon the king of the Amorites , which dwelt in Heshbon , and Og the king of Bashan , which dwelt at Astaroth in Edrei :
On this side Jordan , in the land of Moab , began Moses to declare this law , saying ,
The \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* our God spake unto us in Horeb , saying , Ye have dwelt long enough in this mount :

Turn you, and take your journey , and go to the mount of the Amorites , and unto all \add the places\add* nigh thereunto, in the plain , in the hills , and in the vale , and in the south , and by the sea side , to the land of the Canaanites , and unto Lebanon , unto the great river , the river Euphrates.\f + \fr 1.7 \ft all…: Heb. all his neighbours\f*

Behold , I have set the land before you: go in and possess the land which the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* sware unto your fathers , Abraham , Isaac , and Jacob , to give unto them and to their seed after them.\f + \fr 1.8 \ft set: Heb. given\f* \p
¶ And I spake unto you at that time , saying , I am not able to bear you myself alone :
The \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* your God hath multiplied you, and, behold, ye \add are\add* this day as the stars of heaven for multitude.
(The \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* God of your fathers make you a thousand times so many more as ye \add are\add*, and bless you, as he hath promised you!)
How can I myself alone bear your cumbrance , and your burden , and your strife ?
Take you wise men , and understanding , and known among your tribes , and I will make them rulers over you.\f + \fr 1.13 \ft Take: Heb. Give\f*
And ye answered me, and said , The thing which thou hast spoken \add is\add* good \add for us\add* to do.

So I took the chief of your tribes , wise men , and known , and made them heads over you, captains over thousands , and captains over hundreds , and captains over fifties , and captains over tens , and officers among your tribes.\f + \fr 1.15 \ft made: Heb. gave\f*

And I charged your judges at that time , saying , Hear \add the causes\add* between your brethren , and judge righteously between \add every\add* man and his brother , and the stranger \add that is\add* with him.

Ye shall not respect persons in judgment ; \add but\add* ye shall hear the small as well as the great ; ye shall not be afraid of the face of man ; for the judgment \add is\add* God’s : and the cause that is too hard for you, bring \add it\add* unto me, and I will hear it.\f + \fr 1.17 \ft respect…: Heb. acknowledge faces\f*
And I commanded you at that time all the things which ye should do. \p

¶ And when we departed from Horeb , we went through all that great and terrible wilderness , which ye saw by the way of the mountain of the Amorites , as the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* our God commanded us; and we came to Kadesh-barnea.
And I said unto you, Ye are come unto the mountain of the Amorites , which the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* our God doth give unto us.

Behold , the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* thy God hath set the land before thee: go up \add and\add* possess \add it\add*, as the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* God of thy fathers hath said unto thee; fear not, neither be discouraged. \p

¶ And ye came near unto me every one of you, and said , We will send men before us, and they shall search us out the land , and bring us word again by what way we must go up , and into what cities we shall come.
And the saying pleased me well : and I took twelve men of you, one of a tribe :
And they turned and went up into the mountain , and came unto the valley of Eshcol , and searched it out.

And they took of the fruit of the land in their hands , and brought \add it\add* down unto us, and brought us word again , and said , \add It is\add* a good land which the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* our God doth give us.
Notwithstanding ye would not go up , but rebelled against the commandment of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* your God :

And ye murmured in your tents , and said , Because the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* hated us, he hath brought us forth out of the land of Egypt , to deliver us into the hand of the Amorites , to destroy us.

Whither shall we go up ? our brethren have discouraged our heart , saying , The people \add is\add* greater and taller than we; the cities \add are\add* great and walled up to heaven ; and moreover we have seen the sons of the Anakims there.\f + \fr 1.28 \ft discouraged: Heb. melted\f*
Then I said unto you, Dread not, neither be afraid of them.
The \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* your God which goeth before you, he shall fight for you, according to all that he did for you in Egypt before your eyes ;

And in the wilderness , where thou hast seen how that the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* thy God bare thee, as a man doth bear his son , in all the way that ye went , until ye came into this place.
Yet in this thing ye did not believe the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* your God ,
Who went in the way before you, to search you out a place to pitch your tents \add in\add*, in fire by night , to shew you by what way ye should go , and in a cloud by day.
And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* heard the voice of your words , and was wroth , and sware , saying ,
Surely there shall not one of these men of this evil generation see that good land , which I sware to give unto your fathers ,

Save Caleb the son of Jephunneh ; he shall see it, and to him will I give the land that he hath trodden upon , and to his children , because he hath wholly followed the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*.\f + \fr 1.36 \ft wholly…: Heb. fulfilled to go after\f*
Also the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* was angry with me for your sakes , saying , Thou also shalt not go in thither.
\add But\add* Joshua the son of Nun , which standeth before thee, he shall go in thither: encourage him: for he shall cause Israel to inherit it.

Moreover your little ones , which ye said should be a prey , and your children , which in that day had no knowledge between good and evil , they shall go in thither, and unto them will I give it, and they shall possess it.
But \add as for\add* you, turn you, and take your journey into the wilderness by the way of the Red sea.

Then ye answered and said unto me, We have sinned against the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*, we will go up and fight , according to all that the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* our God commanded us. And when ye had girded on every man his weapons of war , ye were ready to go up into the hill.
And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* said unto me, Say unto them, Go not up , neither fight ; for I \add am\add* not among you; lest ye be smitten before your enemies.

So I spake unto you; and ye would not hear , but rebelled against the commandment of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, and went presumptuously up into the hill.\f + \fr 1.43 \ft went…: Heb. ye were presumptuous, and went up\f*
And the Amorites , which dwelt in that mountain , came out against you, and chased you, as bees do , and destroyed you in Seir , \add even\add* unto Hormah.

And ye returned and wept before the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*; but the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* would not hearken to your voice , nor give ear unto you.
So ye abode in Kadesh many days , according unto the days that ye abode \add there\add*.
